    <p>
        Gathering Our Voices National Aboriginal Youth Conference, hosted by the BC
        Association of Aboriginal Friendship Centres and its Provincial Aboriginal Youth
        Council (PAYC), will be held in Victoria, BC in 2016 on Coast Salish territory. Since the
        event began, the goal for the conference has been simple: give youth the tools to
        work towards a better tomorrow by improving themselves and the world in which
        they live. This event is guided by the BCAAFC’s PAYC who sets the theme, selects
        workshops, and invites facilitators and guest speakers. Having youth at the center of
        the conference, from its inception to the delivery of the event itself, creates an
        authentic and relevant experience for all in attendance.
    </p>

